narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I took BC my junior year in highschool and hadn't remembered much. I'm not very good at math, so I struggled a bit with this course. The tutors weren't great and the teaching was mediocre. Tests were hard.
This is a very difficult course. Be prepared to work.
This course is taken by many people since it is a pre req for lots of majors and premeds so it can be competitive. The curve is better than you expect so dont hesitate.
I would not recommend this course unless you need it to fulfill a major/ requirement. It is not an enjoyable course.
don't take this class unless you have to, but you probably have to
Math 115 is a pretty difficult class. It covers a lot of material, most of which seem to have no relevance to one another. But once you are finished with the course, you sure will feel accomplished.
